223
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:28,325
<i>about something</i>
<i>that only happened to women,</i>

224
00:14:28,742 --> 00:14:32,162
<i>and saying, "This doesn't have to be</i>
<i>this way. We have to change it."</i>

225
00:14:34,915 --> 00:14:38,127
[woman 3] <i>'Cause the laws are made</i>
<i>to keep that woman in her place.</i>

226
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:40,296
[Steinem] <i>And suddenly, you know, that was</i>

227
00:14:40,379 --> 00:14:45,009
<i>a great "aha." You know, I thought,</i>
<i>"Okay, I had this experience.</i>

228
00:14:45,342 --> 00:14:48,304
<i>One in three American women</i>
<i>has had this experience.</i>

229
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:52,433
Why, why is it illegal and dangerous?"

230
00:14:53,517 --> 00:14:58,188
<i>That was kind of the beginning</i>
<i>of the unraveling.</i>

231
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:00,566
[man] You got something to hide?

232
00:15:00,649 --> 00:15:04,528
