233
00:15:04,862 --> 00:15:06,906
[Steinem] <i>The issue is</i>
<i>reproductive freedom,</i>

234
00:15:07,448 --> 00:15:11,994
and that means the right to have children,
as well as the right not to have children.

235
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:14,204
Something really profound is happening.

236
00:15:14,288 --> 00:15:16,457
Mainly that women
have caught onto the game.

237
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:17,917
<i>We don't know it completely yet.</i>

238
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,961
<i>You know, we haven't really discovered</i>
<i>the total anatomy of our oppression</i>

239
00:15:21,045 --> 00:15:24,298
and of what they've been doing to us.
But we do know that it's happening.

240
00:15:24,381 --> 00:15:25,466
We're on to it.

241
00:15:25,549 --> 00:15:26,884
[chanting] Free choice!

242
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:29,553
[woman] <i>This is going to be a battle,</i>
<i>and we will not give up</i>

243
00:15:30,387 --> 00:15:33,807
on the right of a woman
to achieve abortion.

244
00:15:34,266 --> 00:15:38,729
Early feminists... understood immediately

245
00:15:38,812 --> 00:15:42,191
that abortion was a central issue

