251
00:15:53,869 --> 00:15:57,790
It is a political issue,
and the state means to control our bodies.

252
00:15:57,915 --> 00:16:00,167
We produce the soldiers,
we produce the workers,

253
00:16:00,334 --> 00:16:03,504
and they fear the loss of that control.

254
00:16:03,921 --> 00:16:06,090
<i>It's the basis of democracy</i>

255
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:08,550
that you control your own body.

256
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:14,056
And it's the basis of hierarchy
and totalitarian regimes that you don't.

257
00:16:14,723 --> 00:16:16,892
[woman 1] Safe legal abortions
are not available to our--

258
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:19,144
[man] All right. Will you please sit down
or be removed--

259
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:20,980
No, we aren't gonna sit down.
Why don't you--

260
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:23,732
[woman 2] A woman gets pregnant
and she's treated like a criminal.

261
00:16:23,816 --> 00:16:25,150
She can't get an abortion.

262
00:16:25,401 --> 00:16:28,988
She has to go through having that child,
whether she wants it or not.

263
00:16:30,698 --> 00:16:33,742
[Greenhouse] <i>Before the courts</i>
<i>got involved in the abortion issue,</i>

264
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:38,122
it looked as if the matter
would be settled in politics.

265
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:43,919
California passed a new liberalized
abortion law today.

266
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:50,426
<i>California Governor Ronald Reagan</i>
<i>actually signed a reform bill.</i>

267
00:16:53,345 --> 00:16:55,806
<i>I think one thing that people</i>
<i>don't realize today</i>

268
00:16:55,889 --> 00:16:59,727
<i>is that it was the Republican Party</i>
<i>that was the pro-choice party.</i>

269
00:17:03,731 --> 00:17:08,527
<i>And there were states with Republican</i>
<i>governors who passed abortion reforms.</i>

270
00:17:09,611 --> 00:17:13,782
<i>And then New York totally repealed</i>
<i>the old 19th-century abortion law.</i>

271
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:16,910
[reporter] <i>…one of the nation's</i>
<i>most sweeping abortion control bills.</i>

272
00:17:17,536 --> 00:17:20,831
[Rev. Davis]<i> The New York law said</i>
<i>you can have an abortion</i>

273
00:17:20,956 --> 00:17:24,501
<i>throughout the first two trimesters</i>
<i>just if you wanted.</i>

274
00:17:24,752 --> 00:17:27,421
<i>You don't have to give a reason</i>
<i>or anything. It's your choice.</i>

275
00:17:29,423 --> 00:17:32,384
And on July 1st, 1970,

276
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:34,887
the first legal abortion clinic
in America

277
00:17:34,970 --> 00:17:36,889
was opened by the clergy of New York City.

278
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:42,936
<i>And that clinic did over</i>
<i>a hundred abortions a day</i>

279
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:44,897
<i>for 13 months,</i>

280
00:17:45,689 --> 00:17:47,608
<i>until other clinics had formed.</i>

281
00:17:48,108 --> 00:17:50,360
<i>This is the first radical step.</i>

282
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:53,322
<i>And that set off the Catholic Church.</i>

283
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:56,366
[man] I have set before you

284
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:58,827
life and death.

285
00:18:00,329 --> 00:18:02,790
Therefore, choose life.

286
00:18:05,084 --> 00:18:07,836
The unborn
child has no choice.

287
00:18:08,462 --> 00:18:12,091
[man] Does the Catholic Church give you
as much help as you need in this issue?

288
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:15,844
[Greenhouse] <i>The Catholic Church</i>
<i>was very strategic</i>

289
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:17,679
<i>in its opposition to abortion.</i>

290
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:19,515
<i>They set up the Right to Life committee,</i>

291
00:18:19,681 --> 00:18:23,143
and the cardinal and the church
pushed back vigorously.

292
00:18:23,644 --> 00:18:25,729
[Cooke] <i>Legal abortion in New York</i>

293
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:30,484
<i>has already claimed</i>
<i>almost a half million innocent lives.</i>

294
00:18:30,567 --> 00:18:33,904
[Greenhouse] <i>And the New York abortion law</i>
<i>came up in the legislature.</i>

295
00:18:34,029 --> 00:18:37,282
[man] <i>…to abort a human fetus in the womb,</i>
<i>you oughta get sick to your stomach!</i>

296
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:40,786
[woman] <i>There were a lot of</i>
<i>Catholic voters in New York,</i>

297
00:18:41,495 --> 00:18:44,706
and the church was saying,
"We're against abortion."

298
00:18:48,043 --> 00:18:51,171
[man 2] <i>Ours is a nation</i>
<i>with a Judeo-Christian heritage.</i>

299
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:53,966
[Melich] <i>Republicans were in control</i>
<i>of the legislature.</i>

300
00:18:54,174 --> 00:18:57,136
<i>None of this justifies abortion.</i>

301
00:18:57,219 --> 00:19:00,305
[Melich] <i>And now they were repealing</i>
<i>legalized abortion.</i>

302
00:19:00,848 --> 00:19:06,979
The Republicans I knew got angry about
taxes and how big the budget's gonna be.

303
00:19:07,062 --> 00:19:11,733
I think that the traditions
of the Republican Party are the traditions

304
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:14,528
of an individual person to choose
what he wishes,

305
00:19:14,611 --> 00:19:17,030
as long as it doesn't infringe
upon other people.

306
00:19:17,614 --> 00:19:20,868
<i>We were the party</i>
<i>that believed in individual liberty.</i>

307
00:19:21,076 --> 00:19:22,119
[reporter] Congratulations.

308
00:19:22,202 --> 00:19:24,788
<i>[Meliche] Governor Rockefeller</i>
<i>was pro-choice.</i>

309
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:25,956
One more committee...

310
00:19:26,039 --> 00:19:27,875
And we felt, "Why should the state

311
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:30,752
be telling women whether or not
they could have an abortion?"

312
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:33,755
<i>Rockefeller vetoed the bill…</i>

313
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:40,137
<i>and abortion stayed legal in New York.</i>

314
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:46,393
There was a Gallup poll
in the summer of 1972

315
00:19:47,144 --> 00:19:49,563
that asked people to answer the question,

316
00:19:49,897 --> 00:19:53,984
"Do you believe that abortion should be
a matter between a woman and her doctor?"

317
00:19:54,902 --> 00:19:58,572
<i>Republicans by about two-thirds</i>
<i>said yes to that question,</i>

318
00:19:58,822 --> 00:20:02,284
<i>"Abortion should be a matter left</i>
<i>to a woman and her doctor."</i>

319
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:04,536
<i>Not the government.</i>

320
00:20:19,092 --> 00:20:21,303
[man] <i>I think I'm probably</i>
<i>the oldest provider</i>

321
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:23,180
<i>of abortion services in the country.</i>

322
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:28,810
<i>I did my first abortion in 1967.</i>

323
00:20:28,894 --> 00:20:30,395
<i>Illegal abortion.</i>

324
00:20:33,148 --> 00:20:37,110
<i>The Clergy Consultation called,</i>
<i>and they asked me,</i>

325
00:20:37,194 --> 00:20:41,406
<i>"Curtis, would you</i>
<i>consider doing abortions?"</i>

326
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:44,243
Do you have any problems
you want to discuss with me?

327
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:45,953
<i>So, that's where it started.</i>

328
00:20:47,579 --> 00:20:51,124
<i>And I thought I could go to prison,</i>
<i>I could lose my medical license.</i>

329
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:55,837
<i>And I grew up religious.</i>
<i>I became an ordained minister</i>

330
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:57,589
<i>my senior year in high school.</i>

331
00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:02,636
<i>And I think the basic Christian teaching</i>
<i>is compassion and service.</i>

332
00:21:03,262 --> 00:21:07,307
My head and my heart and my hands
said to do this. I can make a difference,

333
00:21:07,391 --> 00:21:09,851
and I'm going take the risk.

334
00:21:12,813 --> 00:21:14,982
<i>I've done this work ever since.</i>

335
00:21:16,692 --> 00:21:20,195
<i>I'm now 80 years old.</i>
<i>And after 80 years, I've decided</i>

336
00:21:20,821 --> 00:21:24,074
I'm not moving on to another career.
I think this is it.

337
00:21:24,157 --> 00:21:25,450
I mean, I'm still needed.

338
00:21:28,245 --> 00:21:30,455
[woman] <i>Thank you for calling</i>
<i>the Southwestern Women's Surgery Center.</i>

339
00:21:30,539 --> 00:21:31,832
I'm Alicia. How may I help you?

340
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:36,586
Okay. I have availability
for tomorrow afternoon...

341
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:42,426
[Dr. Boyd] <i>I've been urged by people</i>
<i>to pass on</i>

342
00:21:42,509 --> 00:21:44,803
<i>what I have learned and experienced.</i>

343
00:21:44,886 --> 00:21:48,890
<i>So, that's what I'm doing, trying to teach</i>
<i>as many young doctors as I can.</i>

344
00:21:48,974 --> 00:21:50,976
…dilate carefully…

345
00:21:51,059 --> 00:21:54,396
<i>My philosophy is that the goal</i>
<i>in providing abortions</i>

346
00:21:54,688 --> 00:21:58,900
<i>is to assist the woman in making</i>
<i>the best decision she can</i>

347
00:21:59,151 --> 00:22:00,569
for her and her life...

348
00:22:01,236 --> 00:22:02,821
in whatever that takes.

349
00:22:06,116 --> 00:22:09,870
[man] <i>The most important moral question of</i>
<i>the abortion debate</i>

350
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:12,289
<i>is what is in the womb?</i>

351
00:22:12,414 --> 00:22:16,835
<i>Is it a person? Does it deserve our</i>
<i>moral attention and protection or not?</i>

352
00:22:16,918 --> 00:22:18,337
<i>That is the most important question.</i>

353
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:21,590
<i>In the pro-life movement,</i>
<i>we're outraged, because we believe</i>

354
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:23,800
<i>that elective abortion is</i>

355
00:22:23,884 --> 00:22:25,761
the taking of an innocent human life.

356
00:22:25,844 --> 00:22:29,514
That is an act of injustice that
we can stop and we need to stop.

357
00:22:29,598 --> 00:22:32,100
-This is Doctor Boyd.
-Dr. Boyd.

358
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:34,936
If you have questions,
we want you to let us know.

359
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:37,981
And we'll take good care of you
and make this...

360
00:22:38,065 --> 00:22:40,442
Women continue a pregnancy
and have a baby,

361
00:22:40,525 --> 00:22:42,986
because they want a baby at that time.

362
00:22:44,112 --> 00:22:46,990
<i>And they have an abortion</i>
<i>because they don't want to be pregnant</i>

363
00:22:47,074 --> 00:22:49,659
<i>at that time in their life</i>
<i>for their own sufficient reasons.</i>

364
00:22:49,743 --> 00:22:51,620
[Dr. Boyd] The state of Texas requires

365
00:22:51,703 --> 00:22:55,957
that you be seen at least 24 hours
before your abortion.

366
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:59,127
And then I'm gonna show you
this sonogram.

367
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:01,838
[woman] That looks like
between five and six weeks, okay?

368
00:23:02,672 --> 00:23:06,468
Sonogram technology is one of the best
friends of the pro-life movement.

369
00:23:06,551 --> 00:23:11,264
It is changing a generation's mind about
what's going on in the womb of a woman.

370
00:23:11,932 --> 00:23:15,394
<i>It is very common for expecting mothers</i>
<i>to have sonograms</i>

371
00:23:15,477 --> 00:23:19,773
<i>on their fridge for children to know what</i>
<i>that picture is. That is their sibling.</i>

372
00:23:19,856 --> 00:23:23,652
<i>And so this was a great tool that we</i>
<i>wanted to tap into and to use,</i>

373
00:23:23,735 --> 00:23:27,489
<i>and we saw that abortion clinics</i>
<i>were already using sonogram technology</i>

374
00:23:27,572 --> 00:23:28,824
<i>before an abortion.</i>

375
00:23:29,783 --> 00:23:32,452
<i>Good morning, everybody.</i>
<i>John Seago with tech...</i>

376
00:23:32,536 --> 00:23:36,373
<i>We think very deliberately about what are</i>
<i>we doing that is taking a step forward</i>

377
00:23:36,456 --> 00:23:39,418
<i>to challenging the very foundations</i>
<i>of Roe v. Wade.</i>

378
00:23:39,501 --> 00:23:42,504
And the sonogram bill was an important one
because we were pushing how much

379
00:23:42,587 --> 00:23:44,923
<i>we can require a physician to do.</i>

380
00:23:45,006 --> 00:23:49,386
All right. So Chapter 171 of the Texas
Health and Safety Code require that

381
00:23:49,469 --> 00:23:53,098
I provide you with this information
at least 24 hours prior to your procedure.

382
00:23:53,181 --> 00:23:56,017
[Seago] We wanted the sonogram
not just to be performed,

383
00:23:56,101 --> 00:23:58,812
for the sake of the abortionist,
but also to be displayed

384
00:23:58,895 --> 00:24:01,064
for the woman to see.
